headlines.description: — Julius Randle scored 31 points, including eight straight during a key fourth-quarter stretch, to lead the New York Knicks to a 103-96 victory over the short-handed Philadelphia 76ers on Monday night.
— DeMar DeRozan scored 28 points, Zach LaVine added 24 and the Chicago Bulls used a 42-point fourth quarter to pull away for a 118-95 victory over the Brooklyn Nets on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bulls pull away in 4th, win 118-95 to snap Nets' 5-game run

headlines.description: — Ja Morant scored 33 points, reserve Brandon Clarke had 20 points and nine rebounds, and the Memphis Grizzlies put together a furious fourth-quarter rally before defeating the Minnesota Timberwolves 125-118 in overtime on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Grizzlies rally to top Timberwolves in OT, 125-118

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Dallas Mavericks

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic scored 25 points, Tim Hardaway Jr. and Jalen Brunson added 17 apiece and the Dallas Mavericks overcame a sluggish start for a 108-92 victory over the New Orleans Pelicans on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic, Mavs overcome slow start, beat Pelicans 108-92

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 25 points, 15 rebounds and 10 assists before the NBA MVP was ejected for violently slamming his shoulder into Markieff Morris, and the Denver Nuggets beat the Miami Heat 113-96 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic, Morris fracas mars Nuggets' 113-96 win over Heat

events.name: Atlanta Hawks at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Cameron Payne scored a season-high 24 points in 22 minutes off the bench and the Phoenix Suns got help from an overturned call to win their fifth straight game, beating the Sacramento Kings 109-104 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Suns hold off Kings 109-104 with help from overturned call

events.name: Charlotte Hornets at Los Angeles Lakers
